  "text": "Generally, tomato is being used as a biological indicator plant for conducting pathogenicity test of R. solanacearum [CITATION_1] and recently eggplant (cv. Agassaim) was used to assay pathogenicity of R. solanacearum. The present study has an evident that, eggplant cultivar (cv. Chaman 363) can be used for pathogenicity test along with tomato which confirm the earlier results of [CITATION_2] .",
